1
00:00:00,310 --> 00:00:01,610
(All people, incidents,
and backgrounds...)

2
00:00:01,610 --> 00:00:03,240
(in this drama are fictitious
and unrelated to reality.)

3
00:00:03,310 --> 00:00:05,380
(Also, children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

4
00:00:19,620 --> 00:00:20,990
(Episode 14)

5
00:00:22,590 --> 00:00:23,600
Jin Ju?

6
00:00:26,030 --> 00:00:27,030
Jin Ju.

7
00:00:31,900 --> 00:00:32,900
Jin Ju.

8
00:00:33,910 --> 00:00:34,910
Jin Ju...

9
00:00:36,110 --> 00:00:37,780
Jin Ju...

10
00:00:39,410 --> 00:00:40,410
Jin Ju.

11
00:00:43,820 --> 00:00:46,520
What in the world are you wearing?
Take it off right now.

12
00:00:47,490 --> 00:00:48,520
My goodness.

13
00:00:48,590 --> 00:00:51,790
You went all the way
to Europe to study...

14
00:00:51,790 --> 00:00:53,160
and for what?

15
00:00:53,460 --> 00:00:56,560
Come on, this is clearly
the British royal look.

16
00:00:56,730 --> 00:00:59,260
The royal look? Like that suits you.

17
00:01:00,030 --> 00:01:01,900
Take it off already!

18
00:01:02,570 --> 00:01:05,400
See? What did I tell you?
I knew this was a bad idea.

19
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:07,370
You're no better, Dad.

20
00:01:08,040 --> 00:01:10,240
Take off that tacky bow tie.

21
00:01:12,080 --> 00:01:13,810
It's not tacky.

22
00:01:15,310 --> 00:01:17,750
We're about to become in-laws
with Adele Group.

23
00:01:18,450 --> 00:01:19,780
Could you please...

24
00:01:19,780 --> 00:01:22,950
make an effort so we don't
look foolish next to them?

25
00:01:28,790 --> 00:01:29,790
Unbelievable.

26
00:01:54,090 --> 00:01:55,720
This is harder...

27
00:01:56,690 --> 00:01:57,890
than I thought.

28
00:01:59,260 --> 00:02:02,760
I wanted to smile for you
as my true self today.

29
00:02:04,060 --> 00:02:05,900
As if it were a final goodbye,

30
00:02:07,200 --> 00:02:09,300
I wanted to smile for you.

31
00:02:10,470 --> 00:02:11,470
No.

32
00:02:12,970 --> 00:02:13,970
No!

33
00:02:19,210 --> 00:02:21,050
Min Jun, you're already here...

34
00:02:22,480 --> 00:02:23,580
Park Min Jun!

35
00:02:25,950 --> 00:02:27,390
Park Min Jun?

36
00:02:37,400 --> 00:02:38,460
Jin Ju.

37
00:02:39,400 --> 00:02:43,170
Jin Ju...

38
00:02:47,940 --> 00:02:48,940
Jin Ju.

39
00:03:05,990 --> 00:03:07,890
- Are you serious?
- What's your problem? Hey!

40
00:03:09,190 --> 00:03:10,630
Watch where you're going.

41
00:03:18,600 --> 00:03:19,600
What is this?

42
00:04:01,780 --> 00:04:04,280
The person you have called
is unavailable.

43
00:04:20,900 --> 00:04:24,600
It looks like our son-in-law
had something urgent come up.

44
00:04:25,140 --> 00:04:27,440
Yes, I'm very sorry.

45
00:04:27,640 --> 00:04:32,110
Not at all.
We completely understand.

46
00:04:33,340 --> 00:04:36,910
Still, this is just plain rude.

47
00:04:37,520 --> 00:04:38,880
Honey, please.

48
00:04:39,280 --> 00:04:40,950
No matter how busy he is,

49
00:04:40,950 --> 00:04:42,620
he should've at least greeted us.

50
00:04:42,890 --> 00:04:45,490
He stormed right past us.

51
00:04:45,490 --> 00:04:47,630
Talk about disrespectful.

52
00:04:49,090 --> 00:04:50,090
Stop it.

53
00:04:54,300 --> 00:04:56,330
Ms. Choi, what do you want to do?

54
00:04:57,870 --> 00:04:59,540
He's a disrespectful brat.

55
00:05:01,070 --> 00:05:03,940
If you can't handle that,
you're free to cancel the wedding.

56
00:05:11,520 --> 00:05:13,220
I'm sorry, Chairman Park.

57
00:05:14,020 --> 00:05:15,050
My mother...

58
00:05:17,960 --> 00:05:19,520
misspoke.

59
00:05:20,590 --> 00:05:23,090
What? Yu Na, you...

60
00:05:25,530 --> 00:05:27,600
If you insist on this marriage,

61
00:05:27,900 --> 00:05:30,100
you need to do better, Ms. Choi.

62
00:05:30,740 --> 00:05:34,310
If you're so helpless that you can't do
anything without my help,

63
00:05:34,810 --> 00:05:36,340
you have no place
as a daughter-in-law...

64
00:05:37,510 --> 00:05:38,940
in this family.

65
00:05:47,950 --> 00:05:49,950
Perhaps we should call it a day.

66
00:05:50,660 --> 00:05:53,560
- I'll reschedule the gathering.
- Sure.

67
00:05:53,890 --> 00:05:55,030
Well then.

68
00:06:16,450 --> 00:06:17,520
Myung Hui, are you...

69
00:06:18,620 --> 00:06:20,490
unhappy about this marriage too?

70
00:06:22,650 --> 00:06:25,520
Not at all.
We'll proceed as planned.

71
00:06:26,820 --> 00:06:28,090
Then...

72
00:06:29,290 --> 00:06:32,600
get Min Jun to these things,
even if it's only his empty shell.

73
00:06:34,500 --> 00:06:35,970
Rather than leaving it
to that Choi Yu Na,

74
00:06:36,230 --> 00:06:38,870
it'd be faster
if you handled it, Myung Hui.

75
00:06:39,770 --> 00:06:40,770
Later.

76
00:07:13,540 --> 00:07:14,540
Right.

77
00:07:15,270 --> 00:07:16,970
I'm sophisticated.

78
00:07:17,310 --> 00:07:19,710
Yes, I'm a sophisticated lady.

79
00:07:20,910 --> 00:07:21,910
Come on.

80
00:07:22,280 --> 00:07:23,480
Listen, sweetie.

81
00:07:24,580 --> 00:07:28,390
I get that you're crazy about him,

82
00:07:28,590 --> 00:07:32,490
but should you be shaming
your own mother?

83
00:07:32,690 --> 00:07:33,960
You're one to talk.

84
00:07:34,630 --> 00:07:37,960
You know full well how much
I've put into this engagement.

85
00:07:39,460 --> 00:07:40,900
Why are you trying to ruin it?

86
00:07:41,530 --> 00:07:43,600
Why you... The nerve!

87
00:07:44,770 --> 00:07:46,800
Hold on. No, let me go.

88
00:07:46,970 --> 00:07:50,170
Who do you think ruined this?

89
00:07:50,240 --> 00:07:52,710
It was
that obnoxious fiance of yours.

90
00:07:52,810 --> 00:07:55,210
He's the one
who should be apologizing,

91
00:07:55,280 --> 00:07:57,380
so why are you cowering?

92
00:07:57,380 --> 00:08:01,050
What do we have to be ashamed of?

93
00:08:02,820 --> 00:08:04,460
They're the ones marrying down.

94
00:08:08,730 --> 00:08:10,560
This is the Adele Group
we're talking about.

95
00:08:12,260 --> 00:08:14,130
You clearly have no idea,

96
00:08:14,200 --> 00:08:16,870
but you'll regret
underestimating Chairman Park.

97
00:08:17,500 --> 00:08:19,440
He's an extremely dangerous man.

98
00:08:19,500 --> 00:08:22,910
For crying out loud,
you're such a coward.

99
00:08:23,070 --> 00:08:24,910
You're so scared of Chairman Park...

100
00:08:24,910 --> 00:08:27,310
that you follow him around
like a lost puppy.

101
00:08:28,180 --> 00:08:29,250
A lost puppy?

102
00:08:33,890 --> 00:08:34,890
Sit back down.

103
00:08:35,990 --> 00:08:36,990
Choi Yu Na.

104
00:08:37,760 --> 00:08:38,790
You have...

105
00:08:39,490 --> 00:08:41,030
no reason to be intimidated.

106
00:08:41,190 --> 00:08:43,790
Min Jun's just the son
of a mistress,

107
00:08:43,860 --> 00:08:45,660
so he should be groveling
at our feet.

108
00:08:45,660 --> 00:08:46,730
Mom!

109
00:08:47,630 --> 00:08:48,630
Listen here.

110
00:08:48,830 --> 00:08:52,270
In this marriage,
your father's company shares...

111
00:08:52,340 --> 00:08:54,640
are your dowry.
You know that, right?

112
00:08:55,440 --> 00:08:57,980
You're the one
holding all the cards,

113
00:08:58,010 --> 00:09:01,180
so why are you acting
like a wallflower?

114
00:09:02,480 --> 00:09:04,880
Let me tell you something
about marriage.

115
00:09:05,250 --> 00:09:08,190
Whoever takes control
from the start...

116
00:09:08,250 --> 00:09:10,590
is the one
who wears the pants for life.

117
00:09:10,590 --> 00:09:11,620
So...

118
00:09:12,960 --> 00:09:17,360
use the shares and your affection
to keep him on the hook...

119
00:09:17,430 --> 00:09:19,030
by playing hot and cold...

120
00:09:19,030 --> 00:09:20,430
Forget it!

121
00:09:20,900 --> 00:09:21,900
Goodness.

122
00:09:22,330 --> 00:09:25,670
How can I do that
when I can barely keep him around?

123
00:09:30,910 --> 00:09:31,940
Yu Na!

124
00:09:32,040 --> 00:09:33,980
Honestly, that girl...

125
00:09:34,680 --> 00:09:35,910
Unbelievable.

126
00:09:36,480 --> 00:09:38,550
Don't forget you're a classy woman.

127
00:09:39,480 --> 00:09:41,320
- A classy lady.
- Right.

128
00:09:41,390 --> 00:09:43,020
Sophisticated, my foot. Darn it!

129
00:09:43,590 --> 00:09:44,660
Hey, you little brat!

130
00:09:45,360 --> 00:09:47,660
They say
if you listen to your parents,

131
00:09:47,660 --> 00:09:49,330
you'll have it made.

132
00:09:49,390 --> 00:09:52,200
Where do you get off throwing
such a classless tantrum?

133
00:09:52,260 --> 00:09:55,670
I was worried about you,
and this is how you repay me?

134
00:09:56,030 --> 00:09:59,000
Gosh, let me go.
I'm so furious right now.

135
00:09:59,070 --> 00:10:00,600
That little... Where did she go?

136
00:10:01,570 --> 00:10:03,070
Everything's on track.

137
00:10:03,470 --> 00:10:04,480
It went as planned.

138
00:10:05,680 --> 00:10:08,680
Okay, please go ahead
with the next phase.

139
00:10:24,900 --> 00:10:28,130
Have you had that look
on your face this whole time?

140
00:10:29,170 --> 00:10:31,240
Are you still in pain, unable...

141
00:10:32,040 --> 00:10:33,140
to forget...

142
00:10:33,600 --> 00:10:35,140
Baek Jin Ju?

143
00:10:36,540 --> 00:10:38,710
But even after seeing your face,

144
00:10:39,040 --> 00:10:40,540
I can't let myself be swayed.

145
00:10:41,510 --> 00:10:42,580
Because I'm no longer...

146
00:10:43,780 --> 00:10:45,450
Baek Jin Ju.

147
00:10:56,430 --> 00:10:57,460
Ta-da!

148
00:10:57,900 --> 00:10:59,360
I made it myself.

149
00:10:59,760 --> 00:11:00,770
Next up, seaweed soup.

150
00:11:01,730 --> 00:11:02,730
It's delicious.

151
00:11:03,330 --> 00:11:04,670
Happy birthday, Min Jun.

152
00:11:04,670 --> 00:11:06,940
Happy birthday to you too,
Baek Jin Ju.

153
00:11:07,440 --> 00:11:09,610
No matter when or how
we might have met,

154
00:11:10,240 --> 00:11:11,640
I would've still fallen for you.

155
00:11:16,080 --> 00:11:17,350
Jin Ju...

156
00:11:37,370 --> 00:11:38,740
What happened to you?

157
00:11:44,040 --> 00:11:46,410
I heard you left the gathering
without a word.

158
00:11:47,340 --> 00:11:48,650
You weren't picking up,

159
00:11:48,650 --> 00:11:50,350
and you're not even going
to explain yourself?

160
00:11:54,120 --> 00:11:55,320
Ms. Choi...

161
00:11:56,050 --> 00:11:58,260
You two were close friends,
weren't you?

162
00:11:59,360 --> 00:12:01,530
- You even planned to study abroad.
- No.

163
00:12:02,730 --> 00:12:04,860
Choi Yu Na is completely different
from her.

164
00:12:05,230 --> 00:12:08,270
She's nothing like the friend
who gave me courage and hope.

165
00:12:08,330 --> 00:12:11,370
She's someone
I want nothing to do with.

166
00:12:13,900 --> 00:12:15,470
You've got it all wrong.

167
00:12:20,180 --> 00:12:21,310
I didn't realize...

168
00:12:22,780 --> 00:12:24,920
we'd grown so far apart.

169
00:12:26,620 --> 00:12:29,150
And to think we're only having
this conversation now.

170
00:12:30,620 --> 00:12:32,420
- If I had known sooner...
- Even if you had,

171
00:12:32,420 --> 00:12:33,690
you would've gone through with it.

172
00:12:33,960 --> 00:12:35,530
You say you're sorry and understand,

173
00:12:35,530 --> 00:12:37,090
but you always do the math first.

174
00:12:39,260 --> 00:12:40,870
Didn't you already decide...

175
00:12:41,270 --> 00:12:43,530
it'd be more beneficial
to follow the chairman's orders?

176
00:12:47,970 --> 00:12:50,110
It's getting late.
You should go home.

177
00:12:51,680 --> 00:12:53,140
I still have some work to do.

178
00:12:59,220 --> 00:13:00,890
This won't happen again.

179
00:13:10,630 --> 00:13:13,300
(Head of Division 1, Park Min Jun)

180
00:13:23,470 --> 00:13:27,850
(Jewelry Division,
Director Kim Myung Hui)

181
00:13:29,610 --> 00:13:32,880
So Ms. Choi and Min Jun
were never together?

182
00:13:33,650 --> 00:13:37,620
Then why did she act like
this marriage was guaranteed?

183
00:13:40,060 --> 00:13:41,590
Maybe she had a crush on him...

184
00:13:42,330 --> 00:13:44,730
when he was in love
with someone else.

185
00:13:46,130 --> 00:13:48,100
When this marriage
was first discussed,

186
00:13:48,700 --> 00:13:51,140
I should've talked things through
with him.

187
00:13:51,900 --> 00:13:55,340
Not going abroad really changed him.

188
00:13:55,540 --> 00:13:58,440
He became quiet and distant.

189
00:13:59,610 --> 00:14:02,580
Now I have no excuse
to keep him close,

190
00:14:04,110 --> 00:14:06,980
not when I'm forcing him
into a marriage he doesn't want.

191
00:14:08,290 --> 00:14:12,660
In that case,
why not tell him everything?

192
00:14:13,060 --> 00:14:17,490
You said you'd tell him everything
once you got proof from CEO Baek.

193
00:14:18,330 --> 00:14:21,470
Back then, we had solid evidence,

194
00:14:21,600 --> 00:14:23,800
and I was sure we'd win.

195
00:14:24,400 --> 00:14:28,340
But right now,
we're stuck in this dangerous fight.

196
00:14:28,470 --> 00:14:30,540
It could put him in danger too.

197
00:14:31,310 --> 00:14:35,310
I guess a strategic marriage is safer
than getting revenge.

198
00:14:35,980 --> 00:14:39,780
Besides, those shares came
at the cost of Dr. Baek's life.

199
00:14:40,850 --> 00:14:42,790
Before Choi Sam Sik
sells them off...

200
00:14:42,790 --> 00:14:44,320
or Chairman Park takes them back,

201
00:14:44,860 --> 00:14:46,520
we need to secure them ourselves.

202
00:14:47,590 --> 00:14:51,060
It's just a shame we have to resort
to a strategic marriage.

203
00:14:51,860 --> 00:14:54,200
Even though I'm up
against a monster,

204
00:14:55,170 --> 00:14:56,230
I guess...

205
00:14:56,670 --> 00:14:58,740
I still don't have it in me
to become one.

206
00:15:00,040 --> 00:15:01,470
Each step...

207
00:15:02,710 --> 00:15:04,510
feels heavier and harder.

208
00:15:05,910 --> 00:15:07,880
That's because this is
about Min Jun, too.

209
00:15:08,450 --> 00:15:09,710
You're his mother, after all.

210
00:15:34,310 --> 00:15:37,010
(Jewelry Division,
Director Kim Myung Hui)

211
00:15:39,410 --> 00:15:42,850
(Dear Chloe Lee)

212
00:15:59,200 --> 00:16:02,000
I've contacted the Adele Group,
just as we planned.

213
00:16:02,930 --> 00:16:03,930
So...

214
00:16:04,770 --> 00:16:06,500
that means everything's ready.

215
00:16:06,700 --> 00:16:07,740
That's right.

216
00:16:08,370 --> 00:16:09,470
How are you feeling?

217
00:16:11,740 --> 00:16:13,040
My heart's racing,

218
00:16:16,480 --> 00:16:17,580
and I'm kind of excited.

219
00:16:20,950 --> 00:16:22,950
Excited about revenge, are you?

220
00:16:23,420 --> 00:16:24,420
James.

221
00:16:25,420 --> 00:16:29,230
They say "revenge" has
two hidden meanings.

222
00:16:30,890 --> 00:16:31,900
One...

223
00:16:32,530 --> 00:16:33,960
is "recovery."

224
00:16:35,500 --> 00:16:37,870
The healing of one's wounds.

225
00:16:39,140 --> 00:16:42,540
The wounds from the unjust loss
of the family you loved.

226
00:16:43,610 --> 00:16:46,180
The injustice, the anger,

227
00:16:47,410 --> 00:16:50,450
the longing, and the guilt.

228
00:16:51,720 --> 00:16:54,520
All those wounds that make my heart
feel like it's burning to ashes.

229
00:16:54,850 --> 00:16:56,150
It's about recovering from those.

230
00:16:58,190 --> 00:16:59,720
And the other one...

231
00:17:01,060 --> 00:17:02,330
is "to return."

232
00:17:04,500 --> 00:17:05,600
To my enemies,

233
00:17:06,860 --> 00:17:08,630
it means I'm coming back for them.

234
00:17:15,240 --> 00:17:17,340
After everything I've endured,

235
00:17:20,410 --> 00:17:21,410
I've...

236
00:17:23,610 --> 00:17:25,220
finally made it here.

237
00:17:34,960 --> 00:17:36,130
One step...

238
00:17:39,700 --> 00:17:40,730
at a time,

239
00:17:43,300 --> 00:17:45,870
I'll return to the lives of those
who killed my father,

240
00:17:48,310 --> 00:17:49,640
my heart racing...

241
00:17:50,770 --> 00:17:52,180
with excitement.

242
00:18:17,200 --> 00:18:18,270
Hey, brother.

243
00:18:19,740 --> 00:18:20,740
Hold on.

244
00:18:21,440 --> 00:18:23,210
You look like
you didn't sleep a wink.

245
00:18:24,710 --> 00:18:26,910
Was the family gathering that rough?

246
00:18:27,010 --> 00:18:28,880
Did you set a date?

247
00:18:30,180 --> 00:18:31,280
Beats me.

248
00:18:31,950 --> 00:18:34,550
How can you not know
your own wedding date?

249
00:18:35,420 --> 00:18:39,090
Don't tell me you skipped it.
No, wait.

250
00:18:39,590 --> 00:18:41,490
You left with Secretary Jung.

251
00:18:43,830 --> 00:18:45,660
I went, but when I got there...

252
00:18:50,570 --> 00:18:54,140
It seemed like Jin Ju wanted me
to call it off, so I ducked out.

253
00:18:57,940 --> 00:19:00,510
Breakfast is going to be
a war zone today.

254
00:19:01,680 --> 00:19:04,850
Hey, brother. I've got your back,

255
00:19:05,550 --> 00:19:06,620
so let's survive this.

256
00:19:08,420 --> 00:19:09,420
Come on down.

257
00:19:24,030 --> 00:19:25,040
Park Min Jun.

258
00:19:25,900 --> 00:19:26,900
Yes, Father.

259
00:19:27,910 --> 00:19:30,970
If you don't have the guts
to walk down the aisle,

260
00:19:31,540 --> 00:19:32,680
call it off now.

261
00:19:33,840 --> 00:19:37,110
Bailing on the family gathering
only embarrasses Director Kim,

262
00:19:37,610 --> 00:19:39,450
but if you run
from your own wedding,

263
00:19:40,080 --> 00:19:42,150
you'll bring shame
on the whole family.

264
00:19:43,350 --> 00:19:45,960
He ran away?
From the family gathering?

265
00:19:46,220 --> 00:19:48,630
Oh my. Then the wedding's off.

266
00:19:48,690 --> 00:19:51,530
Ms. Oh, here you go.
Isn't this your favorite?

267
00:19:51,530 --> 00:19:53,700
Here's something juicy
for you to chew on.

268
00:20:14,380 --> 00:20:17,250
May I join you for breakfast?

269
00:20:17,320 --> 00:20:18,360
Unbelievable.

270
00:20:18,690 --> 00:20:20,960
Since you're here,
you might as well sit down.

271
00:20:22,030 --> 00:20:23,130
Thank you.

272
00:20:28,700 --> 00:20:31,740
Hey, I thought
you just had no pride,

273
00:20:31,970 --> 00:20:33,840
but you don't have any shame either.

274
00:20:34,240 --> 00:20:35,470
Tell me about it.

275
00:20:35,770 --> 00:20:39,110
He ruined the family gathering,
and she's still clinging to him.

276
00:20:39,780 --> 00:20:41,140
What do you mean?

277
00:20:42,550 --> 00:20:45,320
Our parents formally met,

278
00:20:45,920 --> 00:20:46,950
and we all agreed...

279
00:20:48,550 --> 00:20:51,520
that the wedding would go ahead
as planned.

280
00:20:53,760 --> 00:20:57,490
Sir, is there a problem
with our wedding?

281
00:20:58,730 --> 00:21:00,200
No, not at all.

282
00:21:00,200 --> 00:21:02,270
I'm fine with it if you are.

283
00:21:13,940 --> 00:21:17,280
I'm sorry, but I'd like
to postpone the wedding.

284
00:21:38,100 --> 00:21:39,900
You want to run the bio division?

285
00:21:40,870 --> 00:21:41,870
Yes.

286
00:21:43,010 --> 00:21:46,180
I'm pretty sure I told you
to focus only on jewelry.

287
00:21:47,210 --> 00:21:48,910
Suddenly you want
the bio division...

288
00:21:48,910 --> 00:21:50,610
and to postpone the wedding?

289
00:21:50,980 --> 00:21:52,250
What is this nonsense?

290
00:22:01,090 --> 00:22:03,990
Exactly. Why the bio division?

291
00:22:05,060 --> 00:22:07,030
What's she scheming now?

292
00:22:07,760 --> 00:22:11,570
Please, we haven't even gotten
to the good part yet.

293
00:22:11,700 --> 00:22:14,570
It's in your best interest
to hear the rest. Come on.

294
00:22:24,280 --> 00:22:26,320
You'd better have
a darn good reason...

295
00:22:27,450 --> 00:22:29,320
for ignoring my direct orders.

296
00:22:30,890 --> 00:22:33,620
Is Chloe a good enough reason
for you?

297
00:22:35,660 --> 00:22:36,660
Chloe?

298
00:22:39,230 --> 00:22:40,300
Chloe?

299
00:22:40,500 --> 00:22:42,770
As in the world-class brand consultant?

300
00:22:43,500 --> 00:22:45,970
She's a genius who turns
every business she touches...

301
00:22:45,970 --> 00:22:46,970
into a global brand.

302
00:22:47,770 --> 00:22:51,880
The Adele Group has been developing
the bio division for our future,

303
00:22:52,310 --> 00:22:55,480
but it hasn't produced
any meaningful results for years.

304
00:22:56,280 --> 00:23:00,680
With Chloe, the bio division
is guaranteed to deliver results.

305
00:23:01,280 --> 00:23:04,320
I've already received a reply
from her expressing interest.

306
00:23:16,270 --> 00:23:17,370
(Jewelry Division,
Director Kim Myung Hui)

307
00:23:17,430 --> 00:23:19,240
(Chloe Lee)

308
00:23:19,300 --> 00:23:20,500
(Re: Adele Group,
Strategic Collaboration Proposal)

309
00:23:20,570 --> 00:23:21,570
(Chloe Lee)

310
00:23:21,640 --> 00:23:26,180
(Jewelry Division,
Director Kim Myung Hui)

311
00:23:34,280 --> 00:23:36,420
If you let me lead the bio division,

312
00:23:36,850 --> 00:23:40,320
I'll bring in Chloe
and turn it into a global brand.

313
00:23:41,460 --> 00:23:45,060
Will it really be that easy
to bring Chloe in?

314
00:23:46,530 --> 00:23:51,170
Even with her world-class status,
she's never revealed who she is.

315
00:23:51,470 --> 00:23:54,300
Even when she won
at the Rebrand 100 Global Awards...

316
00:23:54,540 --> 00:23:56,840
and was named a next-gen leader
by Time magazine,

317
00:23:57,670 --> 00:23:59,040
no photos of her were ever released.

318
00:23:59,810 --> 00:24:03,580
Do you really think you can recruit
someone so reclusive?

319
00:24:05,380 --> 00:24:07,020
It's because it's so difficult...

320
00:24:08,250 --> 00:24:09,950
that I went
against the chairman's orders...

321
00:24:10,490 --> 00:24:12,690
and even asked to postpone the wedding
to take this on.

322
00:24:16,390 --> 00:24:18,030
If we recruit Chloe,

323
00:24:18,500 --> 00:24:21,460
we'll get global attention
right from the start,

324
00:24:21,800 --> 00:24:25,570
and it'll be our best shot
at saving the bio division.

325
00:24:35,710 --> 00:24:37,650
Then bring her on board.

326
00:24:38,620 --> 00:24:40,580
As director of the bio division...

327
00:24:40,580 --> 00:24:41,950
I'll take over as president.

328
00:24:45,020 --> 00:24:47,460
Chloe will be coming in
as the Head of Brand,

329
00:24:47,890 --> 00:24:51,290
so I think I should outrank her.

330
00:24:56,830 --> 00:24:58,840
Fine. Whatever.

331
00:24:59,500 --> 00:25:02,510
Get Chloe, become president,
do whatever you want.

332
00:25:03,770 --> 00:25:06,240
But you don't have to postpone
my wedding for this.

333
00:25:06,310 --> 00:25:08,550
Between the business deal
and the wedding preparations,

334
00:25:09,880 --> 00:25:11,310
if we try to juggle both,

335
00:25:12,720 --> 00:25:14,220
we might mess everything up.

336
00:25:15,120 --> 00:25:16,220
Director Kim is right.

337
00:25:18,260 --> 00:25:21,660
For now, just focus
on bringing Chloe in.

338
00:25:23,230 --> 00:25:25,630
As for the wedding,
we'll revisit it...

339
00:25:28,130 --> 00:25:29,330
once Chloe is on board.

340
00:25:30,270 --> 00:25:31,300
Sir.

341
00:25:33,200 --> 00:25:34,940
You can't do this to me.

342
00:25:35,270 --> 00:25:38,410
You kept me on a tight leash
and gave me nothing.

343
00:25:39,810 --> 00:25:42,210
I'm not waiting
for your handouts anymore.

344
00:25:43,450 --> 00:25:46,350
The business, the position,
the people I need...

345
00:25:46,980 --> 00:25:48,890
I'll build the power I need...

346
00:25:49,450 --> 00:25:51,120
to take over the Adele Group myself.

347
00:26:01,400 --> 00:26:02,830
Look at you, Ms. Oh.

348
00:26:03,570 --> 00:26:07,400
Director Kim might become president,
and you're acting so calm about it.

349
00:26:07,740 --> 00:26:10,470
She has to bring in
some supposedly amazing person,

350
00:26:10,470 --> 00:26:12,010
this Chloe or whatever.

351
00:26:12,740 --> 00:26:13,880
If it were that easy,

352
00:26:14,140 --> 00:26:16,110
someone else
would've done it already.

353
00:26:16,650 --> 00:26:17,650
You think this is her big chance?

354
00:26:18,350 --> 00:26:20,220
Kim Myung Hui is trying
to show off...

355
00:26:20,220 --> 00:26:22,150
after being passed over
for the promotion.

356
00:26:23,020 --> 00:26:25,560
We delayed the wedding for nothing.
Nothing will change.

357
00:26:36,870 --> 00:26:37,870
Come on.

358
00:26:38,200 --> 00:26:40,900
At least the wedding's postponed.
That's something, right?

359
00:26:42,140 --> 00:26:44,810
Your mother is really
something else.

360
00:26:46,640 --> 00:26:48,950
She just gave you
some breathing room.

361
00:26:58,050 --> 00:26:59,220
Don't get your hopes up.

362
00:27:00,090 --> 00:27:02,190
Whether the Chloe deal
succeeds or fails,

363
00:27:02,560 --> 00:27:04,390
we're getting married
as soon as it's over.

364
00:27:05,960 --> 00:27:07,600
Nothing's going to change.

365
00:27:43,930 --> 00:27:47,300
I'm sorry
this is all I could do for you.

366
00:27:47,970 --> 00:27:49,070
I really am.

367
00:27:50,940 --> 00:27:51,940
No, don't say that.

368
00:27:53,580 --> 00:27:56,210
I should be the one apologizing
for not being...

369
00:27:58,110 --> 00:27:59,120
more helpful.

370
00:28:02,450 --> 00:28:05,760
Back then, I took away
your chance to study abroad,

371
00:28:06,620 --> 00:28:08,990
and I ruined the future
you were dreaming of.

372
00:28:11,330 --> 00:28:12,360
Ever since then,

373
00:28:13,100 --> 00:28:15,600
even though
things have been awkward between us,

374
00:28:17,200 --> 00:28:18,270
you've been...

375
00:28:19,270 --> 00:28:21,540
carrying this burden
all by yourself.

376
00:28:24,440 --> 00:28:26,380
I've always felt so sorry
about that.

377
00:28:41,890 --> 00:28:44,630
Let me help you
bring Chloe on board.

378
00:29:01,980 --> 00:29:02,980
Sure.

379
00:29:10,290 --> 00:29:12,120
(Brand Consultant Chloe Lee,
Let Chloe Lee shape Adele's future.)

380
00:29:12,120 --> 00:29:15,290
After bringing Chloe on board,
Adele's stock has been soaring.

381
00:29:15,360 --> 00:29:17,390
And Director Kim,
who made this deal happen,

382
00:29:17,390 --> 00:29:20,900
- has been named president...
- The genius who stayed hidden.

383
00:29:21,200 --> 00:29:23,370
The news of her appearance
is drawing global attention.

384
00:29:23,370 --> 00:29:25,200
Adele's move has been hailed
as brilliant.

385
00:29:28,470 --> 00:29:30,510
(Brand Consultant Chloe Lee)

386
00:29:31,980 --> 00:29:32,980
Manager Jo.

387
00:29:33,580 --> 00:29:34,580
Yes?

388
00:29:39,850 --> 00:29:41,780
She really is something else.

389
00:29:42,820 --> 00:29:46,060
Looks like Director Kim landed
a real heavy hitter.

390
00:29:46,620 --> 00:29:47,990
I can't believe this.

391
00:29:48,630 --> 00:29:51,630
This Chloe or whatever.
Why was she so easy to get?

392
00:29:52,100 --> 00:29:55,170
Of all people, why did she let
that tramp bring her here?

393
00:29:56,970 --> 00:29:58,400
Who is this woman, anyway?

394
00:30:31,070 --> 00:30:32,770
(Park Min Jun,
Adele's Head of Division 1)

395
00:30:36,540 --> 00:30:40,110
(Park Min Jun, Head of Division 1,
Park Hyun Jun, Head of Division 2)

396
00:30:40,180 --> 00:30:42,880
(Park Min Jun,
Adele's Head of Division 1)

397
00:30:52,990 --> 00:30:53,990
Goodbye.

398
00:30:56,660 --> 00:30:57,890
Goodbye to the old you,

399
00:30:58,800 --> 00:30:59,900
the laughter,

400
00:31:00,860 --> 00:31:01,860
and the memories.

401
00:31:04,030 --> 00:31:05,370
I'm going to erase it all.

402
00:31:07,470 --> 00:31:08,710
There's no need...

403
00:31:10,240 --> 00:31:11,510
for Baek Jin Ju anymore.

404
00:31:39,340 --> 00:31:41,340
(Adele)

405
00:31:42,510 --> 00:31:45,280
Now, it's time to become Chloe.

406
00:32:23,050 --> 00:32:25,950
(Pearl in Red)

407
00:32:26,320 --> 00:32:27,750
Chloe has arrived.

408
00:32:27,750 --> 00:32:29,790
I'm Chloe, the brand consultant.

409
00:32:29,850 --> 00:32:33,090
Chloe is Baek Jin Ju.
She's alive and she's back.

410
00:32:33,160 --> 00:32:34,190
Tell me straight.

411
00:32:34,190 --> 00:32:36,590
Did you see
Baek Jin Ju die that day or not?

412
00:32:36,690 --> 00:32:39,900
It's not like someone can come back
from the dead, right?

413
00:32:39,900 --> 00:32:42,130
Baek Jin Ju is dead. She has to be.

414
00:32:42,300 --> 00:32:45,100
If Chloe is Baek Jin Ju,
it's all over.

415
00:32:45,270 --> 00:32:47,270
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
